    "description": "The Bank of Toyama, Ltd. provides various banking products and services to individual and business customers in Japan. The company offers internet and comprehensive accounts; Super Regular, Super Regular 300, Large Regular, and Toyama Stage Plus; and settlement, current, savings, pension fixed, floating interest rate term, foreign currency fixed term, inheritance, and guardianship system support deposits. It also provides investment trusts, government bonds for individuals, insurance products, Toyama insurance plaza, NISA, individual defined contribution pension plan, financial products intermediary, inheritance, and Toyama Super Best Match products. In addition, the company offers home and renovation, car, educational, free, and card loans; support for formulating business plans and applying for subsidies new businesses, management consulting, and seminar services; business succession and m&a, business matching, recruitment, public assistance, and Toyama Bank Business Club. The company was formerly known as Toyama Industrial Bank and changed its name to The Bank of Toyama, Ltd. in August 1967. The Bank of Toyama, Ltd. was incorporated in 1954 and is headquartered in Takaoka, Japan."
